Blocks.childText: MELODEON. 281 And gladly wander up and down, And smile at toil and pain. I suffer on my three-score years, Till my Deliverer come, And wipe away his servant's tears, And take his exile home. 3 O what hath Jesus bought for me! Before my ravished eyes Rivers of life divine I see, And trees of paradise ! I see a world of spirits bright, Who taste the pleasures there; They all are robed in spotless white, And conq'ring palms they bear ! 4 O what are all my sufferings here, If, Lord, thou count me meet With that enraptured host t' appear, And worship at thy feet ! Give joy or grief, give ease or pain, Take life or friends away ; But let me find them all again In that eternal day. HYMN 230.-L. M. BLESS'D Jesus, what delicious fare- How sweet thine entertainments are !
